This call transfers ownership of the `DerivedGameScreen` instance to the `ScreenManager`, ensuring its lifetime is managed appropriately.

In conclusion, using `std::unique_ptr` in your `ScreenManager` offers strong safety guarantees, aligns with modern C++ practices, and simplifies the management of the polymorphic `GameScreen` inheritance hierarchy. This pattern encapsulates ownership semantics more explicitly than raw pointers and automates cleanup, reducing the risk of memory leaks or other resource management bugs.

